contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:36.669 --> 00:39.038
[♪]

01:05.899 --> 01:07.399
May, I help you?

01:07.400 --> 01:09.902
Yeah, I'd like a girl.

01:09.903 --> 01:11.403
What kind of a girl?

01:11.404 --> 01:14.907
Filthy, I'd like
a really filthy girl.

01:14.908 --> 01:17.910
Fine, my name's Mr. Phil.

01:17.911 --> 01:19.411
I'll be your host
for the evening.

01:19.412 --> 01:21.413
Oh, hi.
Great to see you.

01:21.414 --> 01:24.917
My name is Brr... Buf... Buhhh...

01:24.918 --> 01:26.418
Bubba.

01:26.419 --> 01:28.421
Big ol' Bubba Brown.

01:30.423 --> 01:32.925
Fit as a fiddle and ready for...

01:32.926 --> 01:33.926
you know...

01:33.927 --> 01:35.929
Will this be cash or charge?

01:37.430 --> 01:39.431
Charge?

01:39.432 --> 01:41.934
We accept all
major credit cards, Mr. Brown.

01:41.935 --> 01:44.436
[SCOFFS] You're kiddin'.

01:44.437 --> 01:46.939
Well, we don't take Chevron,
but most anything else will do.

01:46.940 --> 01:49.441
That's good to know. That's
really, like, good to know.

01:49.442 --> 01:50.943
No, I'll go with a lot of cash.

01:52.445 --> 01:54.947
Let's see what I have.

01:54.948 --> 01:56.448
How about room four?

01:56.449 --> 01:57.449
Lovely room.

01:57.450 --> 01:59.451
Does it have a view?

01:59.452 --> 02:00.953
Yes.

02:00.954 --> 02:02.454
Uh, that's too lovely, no view.

02:02.455 --> 02:03.455
They're all the same price.

02:03.456 --> 02:04.957
Okay fine, I'll have
a dark room,

02:04.958 --> 02:06.959
a filthy girl and no view.

02:06.960 --> 02:08.460
How about room one?

02:08.461 --> 02:11.964
Sounds good, room one.

02:11.965 --> 02:13.465
Right over there.

02:13.466 --> 02:14.967
Great!

02:16.469 --> 02:18.470
It's ready right now.

02:18.471 --> 02:19.972
Great, great that it's ready,

02:19.973 --> 02:22.474
'cause I hate waitin' around
for lust and dirt.

02:22.475 --> 02:24.977
Well, enjoy.

02:26.479 --> 02:27.479
Yeah, well, great.

02:27.480 --> 02:29.982
Uh, I'm just gonna wait here
for a second.

02:29.983 --> 02:30.983
I got a friend comin' in here.

02:30.984 --> 02:32.985
We don't allow that,
only one to a room.

02:32.986 --> 02:34.486
Good to know,
that's good to know.

02:34.487 --> 02:36.488
More than one to a room,
I wouldn't even be here.

02:36.489 --> 02:37.489
That's too filthy.

02:37.490 --> 02:38.991
No, I'll just==
Let me just sit here,

02:38.992 --> 02:41.494
and kind of absorb how glad
I am I'm here, you know?

02:52.505 --> 02:54.506
[JAPANESE ACCENT] Oh, herro.

02:54.507 --> 02:56.508
Ah-so, sushi, kimono.

02:56.509 --> 02:59.511
Come here, it's all right,
he's over here with me.

02:59.512 --> 03:01.513
Danny.

03:01.514 --> 03:03.515
Burt?

03:03.516 --> 03:05.017
Don't blow my cover.

03:05.018 --> 03:06.518
That's it?
That's your outfit?

03:06.519 --> 03:08.521
Yeah, pretty good, huh?

03:10.523 --> 03:12.524
That's the most ridiculous
outfit I ever saw.

03:12.525 --> 03:14.526
I can't believe you walked
around like that.

03:14.527 --> 03:16.528
Gimme a little credit, will ya?

03:16.529 --> 03:17.529
I drove.

03:17.530 --> 03:19.531
Drove?

03:19.532 --> 03:20.532
Drove what?

03:20.533 --> 03:22.534
Oh, the, uh...

03:22.535 --> 03:25.037
[CLEARS THROAT]
baghrr-hrr.

03:25.038 --> 03:26.038
What?

03:26.039 --> 03:28.540
The patrol car.

03:28.541 --> 03:29.541
The patrol...?!

03:29.542 --> 03:31.043
Shhhh.

03:31.044 --> 03:33.545
Keep cool.

03:33.546 --> 03:36.548
I can't believe that you drove
around in the patrol car,

03:36.549 --> 03:38.050
dressed like Jerry Lewis.

03:39.552 --> 03:42.554
I didn't drive it Burt,
I rode in the back seat.

03:42.555 --> 03:44.056
Chuck and Bob drove.

03:44.057 --> 03:46.559
Oh, that's much better.

03:47.060 --> 03:49.061
Excuse me,

03:49.062 --> 03:51.563
but, uh, just exactly
what did you have in mind?

03:51.564 --> 03:53.065
Ah, herro.

03:53.066 --> 03:56.068
Toyota, uh, Kawasaki, uh...

03:56.069 --> 03:57.070
Canon AE-1.

03:58.571 --> 04:01.573
Now, listen, give my friend
a dark room

04:01.574 --> 04:04.076
and an ugly girl and no view.

04:04.077 --> 04:05.577
Room two.

04:05.578 --> 04:07.079
Your friend's in room one.

04:07.080 --> 04:08.080
Are they connected?

04:08.081 --> 04:10.083
Why? Are you?

04:11.584 --> 04:14.086
Will I...? No, we'll take it.
No, thanks a lot.

04:14.087 --> 04:15.587
[QUIETLY] Come here, Danny.

04:15.588 --> 04:19.091
Now, listen to me. We meet
at Clancy's Bar in an hour.

04:19.091 --> 04:20.591
Jeez, I don't know
about this Burt.

04:20.593 --> 04:22.094
I'm pretty nervous.

04:22.095 --> 04:24.596
This is a whole new bag
of bananas for me.

04:24.597 --> 04:25.597
Danny, please.
You're a cop.

04:25.598 --> 04:27.099
You have to have nerves of ice!

04:28.101 --> 04:30.602
Huh?

04:30.603 --> 04:32.104
I'm talki" no emotion.

04:33.106 --> 04:35.607
Cold as steel.

04:35.608 --> 04:36.608
All right.

04:36.609 --> 04:37.609
You got it, Dan.

04:37.610 --> 04:38.610
Ready big fella?

04:38.611 --> 04:40.112
Aaah!

04:44.617 --> 04:46.619
Thanks, Burt.

04:54.127 --> 04:55.628
Herro.

05:01.134 --> 05:02.134
Herro?

05:02.135 --> 05:05.137
First five minutes
is 20 bucks extra,

05:05.138 --> 05:06.638
second five is 30 more,

05:06.639 --> 05:07.639
10 per minute after that.

05:07.640 --> 05:10.142
Take off your clothes,
assemble your devices,

05:10.143 --> 05:11.643
if that's your inclination.

05:11.644 --> 05:14.647
Lie down, shut up
and no smoking.

05:16.149 --> 05:18.651
Boy! Boot camp
was easier than this.

05:20.153 --> 05:22.154
If you are a member
of the police department,

05:22.155 --> 05:23.655
please state so now.

05:23.656 --> 05:25.157
Otherwise, you are
committing entrapment,

05:25.158 --> 05:27.159
which is illegal, unethical,

05:27.160 --> 05:30.163
and may I say,
off the record, tacky.

05:33.166 --> 05:34.667
I'm a deputy sheriff.

05:36.169 --> 05:38.670
Welcome to Hedley House.

05:38.671 --> 05:41.173
Hedley House was built in 1903

05:41.174 --> 05:44.176
and was the third building
constructed in Dunn's River.

05:44.177 --> 05:45.677
That's our tour for today.

05:45.678 --> 05:47.179
Thank you and good evening.

05:47.180 --> 05:48.680
Wait, wait.

05:48.681 --> 05:51.183
I'm not here to arrest you.

05:51.184 --> 05:52.684
I just wanna show you
some pictures.

05:52.685 --> 05:55.187
Hey, I'm not into that.

05:55.188 --> 05:57.690
But it's your money, you know.

05:58.691 --> 05:59.691
Oh, no.

05:59.692 --> 06:01.193
It's not what you think.

06:01.194 --> 06:03.695
These are pictures of me
and Sheriff Campbell

06:03.696 --> 06:05.697
in garter belts.

06:05.698 --> 06:07.699
Did you say garter belts?

06:07.700 --> 06:09.701
Yeah, as a matter of fact,
Sheriff Campbell

06:09.702 --> 06:11.703
is in the next room
interrogating a woman,

06:11.704 --> 06:12.704
this very second.

06:12.705 --> 06:14.707
[BURT GIGGLING]

06:19.712 --> 06:21.714
Sounds like a happy man.

06:23.216 --> 06:25.217
Do you know a man named Tibbs?

06:25.218 --> 06:26.718
Tibbs?

06:26.719 --> 06:30.222
Tibbs, no, uh-uh.
No, never heard of him.

06:30.223 --> 06:33.725
Tibbs, uh, doesn't ring a bell.

06:33.726 --> 06:35.727
Wow! Look at the time.

06:35.728 --> 06:38.230
Hey, just hold on here, huh?

06:38.231 --> 06:40.233
You see, uh, me
and the sheriff are...

06:41.234 --> 06:43.235
You know, there's
the sheriff there.

06:43.236 --> 06:46.738
And that's me.

06:46.739 --> 06:47.739
And that's you.

06:47.740 --> 06:49.741
And this is...

06:49.742 --> 06:52.744
I don't know who that is,
but, uh... Hey!

06:52.745 --> 06:56.248
Well, thanks a lot for dropping
by with these, but I gotta run.

06:56.249 --> 06:58.750
Wait a minute, it's you.

06:58.751 --> 07:02.754
Look, it's late and I'm a candy
striper at the VA Hospital.

07:02.755 --> 07:04.256
I found you!

07:04.257 --> 07:05.757
Hey, Burt!
Burt, I found her!

07:05.758 --> 07:07.760
[BURT MOANS]

07:09.762 --> 07:12.264
Look, buddy, I didn't know
you guys were cops.

07:12.265 --> 07:13.765
I don't care about that.

07:13.766 --> 07:16.768
He told us it was a photo layout
for <i>Psychology Today.</i>

07:16.769 --> 07:18.270
It doesn't matter.

07:18.271 --> 07:20.272
I was set up.
So were we.

07:20.273 --> 07:22.774
I thought you guys were actors,
you know, models.

07:22.775 --> 07:23.775
No, Tibbs drugged us.

07:23.776 --> 07:25.277
We were unconscious.

07:25.278 --> 07:26.778
No wonder you didn't respond.

07:26.779 --> 07:31.283
You just lay there smiling,
like a sleeping Scientologist.

07:32.785 --> 07:36.288
Tibbs is blackmailing us
with those.

07:36.289 --> 07:38.790
Please... will you help us?

07:38.791 --> 07:40.792
Do what?
Put him behind bars.

07:40.793 --> 07:42.294
I can't.
Why not?

07:42.295 --> 07:43.295
I just can't.

07:43.296 --> 07:45.297
Tibbs is like a father to me.

07:45.298 --> 07:47.799
If he knew that I squealed,
he'd kill me.

07:47.800 --> 07:49.301
Some father.

07:49.302 --> 07:51.804
I didn't say
he was Robert Young.

07:53.306 --> 07:54.806
What are you afraid of?

07:54.807 --> 07:56.809
Death. Pain and death.

07:57.810 --> 08:00.312
Look, uh...

08:00.313 --> 08:01.313
Gwen.

08:01.314 --> 08:02.314
Look, Gwen,

08:02.315 --> 08:03.815
you help me put him away,

08:03.816 --> 08:06.318
and I'll see to it that
he never bothers you again.

08:06.319 --> 08:07.819
It wouldn't work.

08:07.820 --> 08:09.821
He owns me.
He owns all of us.

08:09.822 --> 08:10.822
That's ridiculous.

08:10.823 --> 08:12.324
People can't own other people.

08:12.325 --> 08:13.325
Oh, yeah?

08:13.326 --> 08:15.827
Well, he owns me.

08:15.828 --> 08:18.330
He's owned me
ever since I was 14.

08:18.331 --> 08:21.833
Help me put him away.
Free yourself.

08:21.834 --> 08:23.835
It can't be done.
<i>You</i> can't do it.

08:23.836 --> 08:25.837
He owns you too.

08:25.838 --> 08:28.340
No one owns me.

08:28.341 --> 08:30.342
And no one will, ever.

08:30.343 --> 08:31.843
Because I say so.

08:31.844 --> 08:33.845
Now, he may beat us
with this thing.

08:33.846 --> 08:35.347
I may end up the laughing stock
of this town,

08:35.347 --> 08:37.849
but no two-bit little pimp
is ever gonna own me.

08:37.850 --> 08:40.852
That was beautiful.

08:42.855 --> 08:44.356
Stupid, but beautiful.

08:46.826 --> 08:48.827
I'm sorry I wasted your time.

08:48.828 --> 08:50.829
Hey, look,
I really feel for you.

08:50.830 --> 08:53.331
I just don't know
what I could do.

08:53.332 --> 08:55.834
Come to the office tomorrow
at noon and make a des...

08:55.835 --> 08:56.835
Dipso...

08:56.836 --> 08:59.337
Deposition.
Right.

08:59.338 --> 09:01.339
Tibbs would shoot me on sight

09:01.340 --> 09:03.341
10 seconds after I left
your office.

09:03.342 --> 09:05.844
I'll give you complete
protection, round-the-clock.

09:07.346 --> 09:08.847
Look, Gwen,

09:08.848 --> 09:11.349
it's no concern of mine
how somebody makes a living

09:11.350 --> 09:13.351
as long as they don't hurt
anybody doing it,

09:13.352 --> 09:16.855
but this guy hurts people,
lots of people.

09:18.357 --> 09:19.358
Please testify.

09:22.862 --> 09:23.862
Noon?

09:23.863 --> 09:24.864
Thanks!

09:34.373 --> 09:35.373
See ya.

09:35.374 --> 09:37.375
Hey, um...

09:37.376 --> 09:38.376
Uh, Danny.

09:38.377 --> 09:42.380
Danny, uh, would you like a...?

09:42.381 --> 09:44.382
You still have
a few minutes left.

09:44.383 --> 09:48.386
I could give you a massage,
a real one, heh,

09:48.387 --> 09:49.388
if you'd like.

09:50.890 --> 09:53.391
Uh, no, no.

09:53.392 --> 09:55.894
I, hu... I better go tell
Sheriff Campbell the good news.

09:55.895 --> 09:57.897
[BURT WHOOPING]

10:00.399 --> 10:01.900
On second thought,

10:01.901 --> 10:04.403
maybe I better just wait
in the lobby.

10:15.915 --> 10:17.917
Herro.

10:18.918 --> 10:22.421
[♪]

10:43.242 --> 10:45.744
Dutch, our chili
needs more meat.

10:45.745 --> 10:48.246
I know, but we can't
afford anymore.

10:48.247 --> 10:50.749
Hmm. Well,
that's too hot.

10:50.750 --> 10:52.250
I'm gonna put
some sour cream in it.

10:52.251 --> 10:54.252
Don't touch my chili!

10:54.253 --> 10:56.755
"My chili"?

10:56.756 --> 10:58.256
Well, I like that.

10:58.257 --> 10:59.758
Since when is it "my chili,"

10:59.759 --> 11:01.760
I could remember when
it was <i>our</i> chili.

11:01.761 --> 11:03.261
All right, our chili,

11:03.262 --> 11:05.764
but our chili is perfect,
so don't mess it up.

11:06.766 --> 11:08.767
Leave that alone.

11:08.768 --> 11:10.268
What do you think, Sandy?

11:10.269 --> 11:11.770
I wouldn't know.

11:11.771 --> 11:14.774
They didn't offer a course in
chili dogs at Le Cordon Bleu.

11:17.276 --> 11:20.278
Saunders, why are you using
our good china

11:20.279 --> 11:21.780
at an outdoor barbecue?

11:21.781 --> 11:24.784
Because you can't afford
paper plates.

11:26.786 --> 11:30.789
Daddy, why do we have to eat
outside anyway, like peasants?

11:30.790 --> 11:32.791
I'm afraid that's what we are,
princess.

11:32.792 --> 11:33.792
We've run out of money.

11:33.793 --> 11:37.295
But Mother has money just
sitting in a bank or somewhere.

11:37.296 --> 11:39.297
That's right,
but only she can withdraw it,

11:39.298 --> 11:41.299
and she's being held prisoner
in some jungle.

11:41.300 --> 11:44.303
Which makes it a little tough
to get to the bank.

11:45.304 --> 11:46.805
Well, this is ridiculous.

11:46.806 --> 11:49.307
There must be some way
to get money.

11:49.308 --> 11:52.811
There is an extreme method that
people have been known to use.

11:52.812 --> 11:54.313
It's called working.

11:57.316 --> 12:00.318
Don't you think
I want to work, Saunders,

12:00.319 --> 12:02.821
to earn my daily bread
by the sweat of my brow,

12:02.822 --> 12:05.323
to work and toil

12:05.324 --> 12:09.327
like all the little common men
across this great land of ours.

12:09.328 --> 12:11.329
But I'm an ex-con.
No one will hire me.

12:11.330 --> 12:14.332
How fortunate for you.

12:14.333 --> 12:18.337
The men appreciate you coming
out to the field, cookie.

12:19.839 --> 12:21.840
We're tired of K rations.

12:21.841 --> 12:24.843
Hey, it's the least I can do for
the boys at the front, major.

12:24.844 --> 12:26.345
Carry on.

12:30.850 --> 12:33.351
You try some, Sandy.

12:33.352 --> 12:35.854
No, thank you.
I'll dine out.

12:35.855 --> 12:38.356
On what? You haven't been paid
in two weeks.

12:38.357 --> 12:41.360
Oh, I am judicious with money.
I've a tidy sum set by.

12:42.862 --> 12:44.363
Really.

12:46.365 --> 12:47.365
Saunders...

12:47.366 --> 12:48.867
Yes.

12:48.868 --> 12:51.369
I was wondering...

12:51.370 --> 12:55.874
See, we're in a spot here,
and I was wondering if maybe...

12:55.875 --> 12:58.877
Well... you know what I mean.

12:58.878 --> 13:00.880
No, I don't.
Clarify yourself.

13:02.882 --> 13:06.885
Well, I was wondering if
you could lend us some money.

13:06.886 --> 13:10.389
Excuse me,
while I consider your request.

13:14.894 --> 13:17.897
[SAUNDERS LAUGHS]

13:18.898 --> 13:20.900
[LAUGHING]

13:25.404 --> 13:26.905
Hi, Mary.
Where's Burt?

13:26.906 --> 13:30.408
He's out, you know, tracking
down the man who framed him,

13:30.409 --> 13:31.910
and trying to force him
to confess.

13:31.911 --> 13:33.411
Hopefully, he won't get killed.

13:33.412 --> 13:35.914
He said he would be by
after he did all that,

13:35.915 --> 13:37.917
or by 6:30,
whichever came first.

13:39.919 --> 13:41.920
Here's the potato salad.
Thanks.

13:41.921 --> 13:43.421
Mary, is that all you brought?

13:43.422 --> 13:44.423
Potato salad?

13:48.928 --> 13:51.931
Uh-oh, the party's over.

13:53.432 --> 13:56.434
Ooh, I'm sorry.
I guess I came at a bad time.

13:56.435 --> 13:58.436
I didn't mean to interrupt
your barbecue...

13:58.437 --> 13:59.438
Leslie.

14:00.940 --> 14:01.940
Hi.

14:01.941 --> 14:03.942
We haven't met.
I'm Annie.

14:03.943 --> 14:06.946
That's Leslie, the young woman
who was trying to kill my son.

14:09.448 --> 14:10.949
Hi, nice to meet you.

14:10.950 --> 14:13.952
It's nice to meet you too.
Are you a relative?

14:13.953 --> 14:15.955
No, a tramp.

14:20.960 --> 14:22.961
Hey, what do you got
in that there box?

14:22.962 --> 14:24.963
Another one of those bombs
that don't go off?

14:24.964 --> 14:27.465
There's a rattlesnake in here!

14:27.466 --> 14:29.467
Mm-hmm.

14:29.468 --> 14:32.470
Look, I really just came
to see Billy,

14:32.471 --> 14:34.973
so just go ahead with your
party and don't mind me.

14:34.974 --> 14:36.474
He's not in at the moment.

14:36.475 --> 14:38.977
He's out rescuing his mother.

14:38.978 --> 14:41.479
From revolutionaries
on a Caribbean island.

14:41.480 --> 14:43.481
Oh, nuts.

14:43.482 --> 14:44.515
Yeah.

14:44.516 --> 14:46.751
And I had such a great plan.

14:46.752 --> 14:48.319
I was gonna give this to him.

14:48.320 --> 14:50.321
I was gonna say
let's forgive and forget.

14:50.322 --> 14:51.823
And then he was
gonna open it up.

14:51.824 --> 14:54.492
And the rattlesnake was
gonna jump out at him!

14:54.493 --> 14:57.562
Wouldn't that have been great?

14:57.563 --> 15:01.567
Leslie, you have just got to
develop some other interests.

15:03.569 --> 15:06.070
It took me weeks
to find a rattlesnake.

15:06.071 --> 15:08.573
I looked all over,
nobody has any.

15:08.574 --> 15:12.744
Well, I... I guess
that's not your problem.

15:12.745 --> 15:15.313
It's been really nice
talking to you, Mrs. Campbell.

15:15.314 --> 15:16.815
Yeah.

15:18.817 --> 15:22.320
Well, once again,
I-I'm sorry for bothering you.

15:22.321 --> 15:24.322
See you soon.

15:24.323 --> 15:25.823
And don't try to follow me!

15:25.824 --> 15:28.326
I've got a gun
and a hand grenade!

15:30.329 --> 15:31.829
Hey, Mare. Hi, everybody.

15:31.830 --> 15:33.331
Oh, Burt, she was just here.

15:33.332 --> 15:34.332
She was?

15:34.333 --> 15:35.833
Quick, get her.

15:35.834 --> 15:38.336
I'm goin', I'm goin'!
Who, what, when, where?

15:38.337 --> 15:39.837
Just now, Burt. Just now.

15:39.838 --> 15:40.838
Who just now?
Who just now?

15:40.839 --> 15:42.340
Leslie.

15:42.341 --> 15:44.342
I don't believe it.
You just let her get away?

15:44.343 --> 15:45.343
That's it?
Which way did she go?

15:45.344 --> 15:47.845
It's too late now, Burt.

15:47.846 --> 15:49.347
Can it be true?

15:49.348 --> 15:52.850
General Doolittle in the flesh?

15:52.851 --> 15:55.353
Forgive my informalities, sir,

15:55.354 --> 15:57.355
but may I join
the rest of America

15:57.356 --> 16:00.358
and congratulate you
on that daring raid on Tokyo?

16:00.359 --> 16:01.360
It was nothing.

16:03.362 --> 16:07.365
You lifted the morale of every
fighting man in the Pacific.

16:07.366 --> 16:10.368
You taught us the real meaning
of the word "Yank."

16:10.369 --> 16:11.869
[CLANG]

16:11.870 --> 16:13.871
Hey, come and get it.

16:13.872 --> 16:15.373
[CLANGING]

16:21.880 --> 16:24.882
Hey, uh, what's the occasion?

16:24.883 --> 16:25.883
Dinner.

16:25.884 --> 16:26.884
Oh.

16:26.885 --> 16:28.887
[RATTLING]

16:29.888 --> 16:30.889
Whoa!

16:37.896 --> 16:39.397
[CLICKING]

16:47.406 --> 16:49.408
Did I get it?

16:51.410 --> 16:54.412
Yes, you did.

16:54.413 --> 16:55.413
In case you were afraid

16:55.414 --> 16:58.416
my big toe posed
any threat to you...

16:58.417 --> 17:00.419
rest assured, you got that too.

17:02.421 --> 17:04.922
Hey, Chester, I mean,
I'm really sorry.

17:04.923 --> 17:09.426
You know, it... really
hasn't dawned on me yet.

17:09.428 --> 17:10.428
I've been shot!

17:10.429 --> 17:11.929
Help me!
Okay.

17:11.930 --> 17:13.431
Help me!
All right. Come on.

17:13.432 --> 17:14.432
Somebody help me!

17:14.433 --> 17:15.933
I'll get you to a hospital.

17:15.934 --> 17:18.435
[SOBBING]
Oh, Mommy! Mommy! Mommy!

17:33.652 --> 17:35.153
[SIGHS]

17:36.155 --> 17:37.155
Hi.

17:37.156 --> 17:39.157
Oh, <i>buenas noches.</i>

17:39.158 --> 17:40.658
<i>De nada.</i>

17:40.659 --> 17:42.661
Please come and have a seat.

17:49.168 --> 17:50.668
Thank you.

17:50.669 --> 17:53.171
You know, I tried to get
a message to your home

17:53.172 --> 17:54.672
in Connecticut, America,

17:54.673 --> 17:56.674
but I don't know if I succeed.

17:56.675 --> 17:58.176
The man I sent never came back.

17:58.177 --> 18:01.179
You mean, you sent a man
to Con-nect-i-cot?

18:01.180 --> 18:04.182
Oh, no, I sent him to
the village, to Western Union,

18:04.183 --> 18:05.683
but...

18:05.684 --> 18:07.685
Oh, he'll come back, I'm sure.

18:07.686 --> 18:10.188
I hope.

18:10.189 --> 18:11.689
I pray he comes back.

18:11.690 --> 18:13.191
Don't worry, really,

18:13.192 --> 18:16.194
everything is going
to turn out just fine.

18:16.195 --> 18:18.696
Well, it's just that
I'm a little upset.

18:18.697 --> 18:19.697
Why?

18:19.698 --> 18:21.699
Well, the CIA,
they promised to come

18:21.700 --> 18:23.701
and help us overthrow
the government here,

18:23.702 --> 18:25.503
and they're late.
I don't know where they are!

18:26.705 --> 18:28.706
Maybe they got stuck in traffic.

18:28.707 --> 18:30.208
I don't know.

18:30.209 --> 18:32.210
I just hope this doesn't
turn out to be

18:32.211 --> 18:33.711
another Bay of Pigs here.

18:33.712 --> 18:34.712
Oh, I'll tell you that.

18:34.713 --> 18:37.715
A Bay of Pigs.

18:37.716 --> 18:39.717
Wouldn't that be terrible?

18:39.718 --> 18:41.219
No, I think
it'd be kind of cute.

18:41.220 --> 18:43.221
I mean, a whole bay
full of little pigs,

18:43.222 --> 18:45.723
all oinking and swimming around.

18:45.724 --> 18:47.725
Jessica, you are wonderful.

18:47.726 --> 18:48.726
Oh.
Yes! Yes, you are.

18:48.727 --> 18:50.728
You're wonderful to try
to cheer me up

18:50.729 --> 18:52.731
with your wonderful
American sense of humor.

18:54.233 --> 18:55.234
Oh.

18:57.236 --> 18:59.737
You know, I was thinking,

18:59.738 --> 19:01.739
why don't I give all this up?

19:01.740 --> 19:05.743
Sure, my men and I can always go
back to our marimba band again.

19:05.744 --> 19:07.746
What do I need this for?

19:08.747 --> 19:10.749
It's something you believe in.

19:12.251 --> 19:14.752
Jessica, don't leave.

19:14.753 --> 19:16.754
I won't.

19:16.755 --> 19:19.757
You won't let me.

19:19.758 --> 19:22.760
Oh, no, I mean tonight,
don't leave.

19:22.761 --> 19:24.763
Stay with me in my tent.

19:27.766 --> 19:29.768
Oh, El!

19:31.770 --> 19:34.272
I don't, uh...

19:34.273 --> 19:35.774
think I could do that.

19:37.276 --> 19:39.777
No, Jessica, don't.
Please don't misunderstand,

19:39.778 --> 19:40.778
It's just that I...

19:40.779 --> 19:42.280
I... I... I worry about you.

19:42.281 --> 19:44.782
I stay up all night thinking
about you in your tent alone

19:44.783 --> 19:46.784
with the mosquitoes
and the Gila monsters and...

19:46.785 --> 19:48.286
Monsters?

19:49.788 --> 19:51.789
You mean, you have
monsters here?

19:51.790 --> 19:52.790
Oh, Jessica...

19:52.791 --> 19:53.791
Whoo!

19:53.792 --> 19:55.793
Please stay with me tonight.

19:55.794 --> 19:57.796
This could be
our last night together.

20:13.312 --> 20:15.314
Here we are.

20:24.323 --> 20:26.824
Now, I...

20:26.825 --> 20:29.327
I just...

20:29.328 --> 20:30.328
fluff up your pillows,

20:30.329 --> 20:32.296
and everything is perfect.

20:32.297 --> 20:33.965
Uh, I...

20:33.966 --> 20:35.733
Would you like another blanket?

20:35.734 --> 20:37.301
Oh, no, no, no blanket.

20:37.302 --> 20:38.369
No blanket.

20:38.370 --> 20:39.370
I, uh...

20:39.371 --> 20:40.371
What about a book to read?

20:40.372 --> 20:42.373
Ah, yes, yes, yes.
Here we have...

20:42.374 --> 20:44.376
<i>El Mundo en la Opinión de Garp.</i>

20:46.578 --> 20:48.145
Well, uh...

20:48.146 --> 20:50.648
if there's anything
that you need or want,

20:50.649 --> 20:52.650
I'll be right over here.

20:52.651 --> 20:54.219
El?
Huh?

20:56.221 --> 20:58.623
I thought, um...

20:58.624 --> 20:59.824
What?

20:59.825 --> 21:02.159
Nothing. Nothing.

21:02.160 --> 21:06.230
No, what my little
piña colada? Tell me.

21:06.231 --> 21:10.234
Well, you see,
I thought we were going to...

21:10.235 --> 21:12.236
share this tent.

21:12.237 --> 21:13.738
Yes, we are.

21:13.739 --> 21:14.739
I'll be right over here.

21:14.740 --> 21:17.241
Uh, El...

21:17.242 --> 21:19.243
what I meant was...

21:19.244 --> 21:22.246
when you said that you
wanted me in your tent,

21:22.247 --> 21:25.750
I thought that you meant you...

21:25.751 --> 21:28.753
wanted me in your tent.

21:28.754 --> 21:30.755
Oh. Oh, m-me.

21:30.756 --> 21:33.257
Oh, n-no, never. You?

21:33.258 --> 21:35.760
But, my Madonna...

21:35.761 --> 21:37.261
No, no, no, no, no, no.

21:37.262 --> 21:38.763
No, no, no.

21:38.764 --> 21:40.765
May the <i>federales</i>
amputate my hands

21:40.766 --> 21:42.767
if ever I dare to touch...

21:42.768 --> 21:46.771
No, no, no, no.
Never, my Jessica, never!

21:46.772 --> 21:48.272
Never?

21:48.273 --> 21:50.775
Nnn... Nnn-nn...

21:52.778 --> 21:53.778
Not...

21:53.779 --> 21:55.280
until we marry.

22:00.285 --> 22:01.786
I see.

22:08.660 --> 22:11.162
[♪]

22:16.835 --> 22:19.837
ANNOUNCER: <i>Now that Danny's found a
hooker who will testify against Tibbs,</i>

22:19.838 --> 22:21.839
<i>will she be afraid</i>
<i>to open her mouth?</i>

22:21.840 --> 22:23.341
<i>Now that Jessica found out</i>

22:23.342 --> 22:25.643
<i>the revolution</i>
<i>may last 72 years,</i>

22:25.644 --> 22:27.712
<i>will she have</i>
<i>her charge account switched?</i>

22:27.713 --> 22:29.714
<i>Now that the Tates</i>
<i>are out of cash,</i>

22:29.715 --> 22:31.716
<i>will Chester sell his sweaters?</i>

22:31.717 --> 22:33.217
<i>Will Billy ever find Jessica?</i>

22:33.218 --> 22:35.820
<i>Will anyone ever find Billy?</i>

22:35.821 --> 22:38.389
<i>These questions and many others</i>
<i>will be answered</i>

22:38.390 --> 22:40.892
<i>in the next episode of</i> Soap.

